q4&quot;&gt;local Hosting: &lt;a href=&quot;https://nodejs.org/en/&quot; class=&quot;css-1od09yo&quot;&gt;node.js&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 class=&quot;css-170hkfz&quot;&gt;What is Jamstack?&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;css-1bkk5q4&quot;&gt;Many of you should have known web platforms like wordpress and wix.com.
Or other traditional web development frameworks like Angular, React, ASP.net.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;css-1bkk5q4&quot;&gt;Entering 2020, there is a revolution in web development industory happening and that is Jamstack.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;css-1bkk5q4&quot;&gt;It emphasizes that the blog data and the template are all separated. The data could be archieved from anywhere through graphql.
In Gatsbyjs, those blog data updates are done in mdx data file with markup. While the UI and CSS styles of the pages are generated webpack by loading those React compoents.
For more detail, please read the recommended reading at the bottom of this page.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;css-1bkk5q4&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-wrapper&quot; style=&quot;position:relative;display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;max-width:950px&quot;&gt;
      &lt;span class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-background-image&quot; style=&quot;padding-bottom:52.5%;position:relative;bottom:0;left:0;background-image:url(&amp;#x27;data:image/jpeg;base64,&amp;#x27;);background-size:cover;display:block&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;img class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-image css-0&quot; alt=&quot;Jamstack&quot; title=&quot;Jamstack&quot; src=&quot;/static/79585a4da8b91af476181827be43b36b/00432/jamstack.jpg&quot; srcSet=&quot;/static/79585a4da8b91af476181827be43b36b/46946/jamstack.jpg 240w,/static/79585a4da8b91af476181827be43b36b/55489/jamstack.jpg 480w,/static/79585a4da8b91af476181827be43b36b/00432/jamstack.jpg 950w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 950px) 100vw, 950px&quot; style=&quot;width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 class=&quot;css-170hkfz&quot;&gt;Install and Develop Steps&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;style data-emotion-css=&quot;15rlv7r&quot;&gt;.css-15rlv7r li{font-size:1rem;-webkit-letter-spacing:-0.003em;-moz-letter-spacing:-0.003em;-ms-letter-spacing:-0.003em;letter-spacing:-0.003em;line-height:1.625;--baseline-multiplier:0.179;--x-height-multiplier:0.35;}@media screen and (min-width:640px){.css-15rlv7r li{font-size:1rem;}}@media screen and (min-width:768px){.css-15rlv7r li{font-size:1.25rem;}}&lt;/style&gt;&lt;ol class=&quot;css-15rlv7r&quot;&gt;&lt;li class=&quot;css-0&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;css-1bkk5q4&quot;&gt;Setting up the environment by following -  &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.gatsbyjs.org/tutorial/&quot; class=&quot;css-1od09yo&quot;&gt;Gatsby Tutorial&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class=&quot;css-0&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;css-1bkk5q4&quot;&gt;Choose a theme starter and install it&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;css-1bkk5q4&quot;&gt;For example, the theme I used - &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.gatsbyjs.org/starters/LekoArts/gatsby-starter-minimal-blog/&quot; class=&quot;css-1od09yo&quot;&gt;gatsby-starter-minimal-blog&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;gatsby-highlight&quot; data-language=&quot;cmd&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;prism-code language-cmd&quot; style=&quot;color:#d6deeb;background-color:#011627&quot; data-linenumber=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;token-line&quot; style=&quot;color:#d6deeb&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;line-number-style&quot;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token plain&quot;&gt;gatsby new minimal-blog LekoArts/gatsby-starter-minimal-blog&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ol start=&quot;3&quot; class=&quot;css-15rlv7r&quot;&gt;&lt;li class=&quot;css-0&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;css-1bkk5q4&quot;&gt;Edit your site with editor and view it through &amp;quot;gatsby develop&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class=&quot;css-0&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;css-1bkk5q4&quot;&gt;Build it through &amp;quot;gatsby build&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class=&quot;css-0&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;css-1bkk5q4&quot;&gt;Publish the site to Github Pages by following - &lt;a href=&quot;https://gist.github.com/TylerFisher/6127328&quot; class=&quot;css-1od09yo&quot;&gt;Basic steps for hosting on Github · GitHub&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;h3 class=&quot;css-170hkfz&quot;&gt;My experience and thoughts&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;css-1bkk5q4&quot;&gt;Before trying out jamstack, I have completed several web application projects using asp.net webform and MVC framework,
and PHP frameworks like wordpress.org and Magento. Comparing with them, jamstack is easier to be picked up at first, it is lightweight and with many beautiful templates which could be chosen from.
However, for template modification and functional changes, it was not easy to start without reading tutorials or any react programming background knowledge.
It took me some time to learn how those plug-ins work, and modify the compoment part.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;css-1bkk5q4&quot;&gt;Generally speaking, I am really eocouraging anyone who are interested in website creation to try out JAMstack. If you could find a template started which suits your needs perfectly, then everything woudl be fine without any coding modification.
Otherwise, it should be a challenge and still it is worth to learn and try. For React developer, it should be a cup of tea =)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;css-1bkk5q4&quot;&gt;Recommended reading:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://snipcart.com/blog/jamstack&quot; class=&quot;css-1od09yo&quot;&gt;The JAMstack in 2020: Why (and How) to Get Started - Snipcart&lt;/a&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;css-1bkk5q4&quot;&gt;Last edited: 24/07/2020&lt;/p&gt;&lt;style data-emotion-css=&quot;13l3oqy&quot;&gt;.css-13l3oqy{background-color:var(--theme-ui-colors-muted,#e2e8f0);border:0;height:1px;margin:1rem;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;}&lt;/style&gt;&lt;hr class=&quot;css-13l3oqy&quot;/&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title><![CDATA[Reinforcement Learning 1]]></title><link>https://durandalsowner.github.io/reinforcement_learning_1</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://durandalsowner.github.io/reinforcement_learning_1</guid><pubDate>Wed, 01 Jul 2020 21:00:00 GMT</pubDate><content:encoded>&lt;style data-emotion-css=&quot;1hycliv&quot;&gt;body{--theme-ui-colors-transparent:var(--theme-ui-colors-transparent,transparent);--theme-ui-colors-black:var(--theme-ui-colors-black,#000);--theme-ui-colors-white:var(--theme-ui-colors-white,#fff);--theme-ui-colors-gray-0:var(--theme-ui-colors-gray-0,null);--theme-ui-colors-gray-1:var(--theme-ui-colors-gray-1,#f7fafc);--theme-ui-colors-gray-2:var(--theme-ui-colors-gray-2,#edf2f7);--theme-ui-colors-gray-3:var(--theme-ui-colors-gray-3,#e2e8f0);--theme-ui-colors-gray-4:var(--theme-ui-colors-gray-4,#cbd5e0);--theme-ui-colors-gray-5:var(--theme-ui-colors-gray-5,#a0aec0);--theme-ui-colors-gray-6:var(--theme-ui-colors-gray-6,#718096);--theme-ui-colors-gray-7:var(--theme-ui-colors-gray-7,#4a5568);--theme-ui-colors-gray-8:var(--theme-ui-colors-gray-8,#2d3748);--theme-ui-colors-gray-9:var(--theme-ui-colors-gray-9,#1a202c);--theme-ui-colors-red-0:var(--theme-ui-colors-red-0,null);--theme-ui-colors-red-1:var(--theme-ui-colors-red-1,#fff5f5);--theme-ui-colors-red-2:var